WEBVTT

00:01.660 --> 00:03.525
REDDINGTON; Fabricio?
Yes, Sir?

00:03.600 --> 00:05.022
They need help
in the back room.

00:05.100 --> 00:06.897
More servers.
At least one. Maybe two.

00:06.970 --> 00:08.335
Yes, sir,
Mr. Reddington.

00:08.400 --> 00:10.231
And, also, let's open
another couple of cases
of the Reserva.

00:12.710 --> 00:13.972
Champagne, the wines,
cocktails.

00:14.040 --> 00:15.302
I don't care if
they're drinking milk...

00:15.380 --> 00:16.574
I don't want an empty glass
out there.

00:16.650 --> 00:17.878
(CHUCKLES) Of course,
Mr. Reddington.

00:17.950 --> 00:19.918
And, Mr. Reddington,
it's good to have
you back, sir.

00:19.980 --> 00:21.777
Oh, it's good to be had.

00:21.850 --> 00:24.080
(JAZZ MUSIC PLAYS)

00:24.150 --> 00:25.879
Nolan! You made it!

00:25.950 --> 00:28.214
Thank you for coming.
Wouldn't miss it
for the world.

00:28.290 --> 00:30.281
(LAUGHS)
Wonderful party, Red.

00:30.360 --> 00:33.955
Not nearly as wonderful
as your daughter's
beautiful wedding in Berlin.

00:34.030 --> 00:35.895
My head's still throbbing.

00:35.960 --> 00:38.167
Vivian,
where's your husband?

00:38.230 --> 00:40.130
He couldn't make it.
Thank goodness.

00:40.200 --> 00:42.998
Find me later.
We have some
catching up to do.

00:43.070 --> 00:45.004
Red! Hey! Red!

00:45.070 --> 00:48.005
Teddy!
I can't hear a damn thing
with all this music!

00:48.080 --> 00:49.843
It's much quieter
on the veranda.

00:49.910 --> 00:51.571
Miranda's in the toilet!

00:51.650 --> 00:54.016
The balcony.
It's much quieter outside.

00:54.080 --> 00:55.843
Forget it!
I'll be out on the veranda!

00:55.920 --> 00:57.342
I can't hear a_ word
you're sayIn'!

00:59.320 --> 01:01.015
Oh.
Uh, Mr. Reddington.

01:01.090 --> 01:03.979
Hey. Help me out. I'm looking
for a girl on the wait staff.

01:04.060 --> 01:05.482
_ A brunette
With a nose rIng?

01:05.560 --> 01:07.619
Sidney.
Yeah, Sidney.

01:07.700 --> 01:10.123
Think you could
introduce me to Sidney?
Funny thing, that.

01:10.200 --> 01:12.498
She asked me to
introduce her to you.

01:12.570 --> 01:14.333
Oh.
Heddie!

01:14.400 --> 01:16.630
Would you be a dear
and introduce Vontae

01:16.710 --> 01:18.701
to your young
waitress friend?

01:18.770 --> 01:22.547
Oh, my God. Will you
come with me
and meet this girl already?

01:22.610 --> 01:26.774
She has been making eyes
at you all night.
She has?

01:26.850 --> 01:29.045
MAN: Heard about
the break-out, Red!
Genius!

01:29.120 --> 01:30.644
How many lives
do you have anyway?

01:30.720 --> 01:34.053
(CHUCKLES) Honestly, Roger,
I lost count
at a baker's dozen.

01:34.120 --> 01:36.122
Give my regards
to the captain.

01:36.190 --> 01:37.282
Good to see you guys.

01:38.030 --> 01:39.952
Hey! There you are.

01:40.030 --> 01:41.657
We've got a situation
at the buffet.

01:41.730 --> 01:44.290
Oh, dear. What's wrong?
You're out of those
Jumbo shrimps.

01:44.370 --> 01:45.826
I let the kitchen know.

01:45.900 --> 01:47.060
(CHUCKLES)

01:47.140 --> 01:50.007
Hey, uh, while I got ya,
I've been meaning to apologize

01:50.070 --> 01:51.469
about that whole
Jury mix-up.

01:51.540 --> 01:53.701
I feel real bad.
Eh. It's behind us.

01:53.780 --> 01:55.077
Mmm-mmm.
Not to me, it's not.

01:55.140 --> 01:56.801
I dropped the ball.
Screwed the pooch.

01:56.880 --> 01:59.474
Bungled the job.
If there's anything you need,

01:59.550 --> 02:02.815
any way I can
make it up to you,
just let ol' Jelly Bean know.

02:02.890 --> 02:05.643
Thank you for coming, Glen.
No problemo.

02:05.720 --> 02:08.086
Hey. I thought
you'd want me here.

02:08.160 --> 02:10.822
I'm sort of the straw
that stirs the drink.

02:10.890 --> 02:14.223
(BOTH CHUCKLE)
By the way, Mom's over
at the punch bowl.

02:14.300 --> 02:17.758
She's always
had her eye on ya,
if you know what I mean.

02:18.770 --> 02:19.862
(CELL PHONE RINGS)
Drop by. Say hi.

02:19.940 --> 02:21.999
And don't forget
the shrimps. (CHUCKLES)

02:22.070 --> 02:23.708
(RINGING CONTINUES)

02:23.770 --> 02:25.203
Dembe. Did you find it?

02:25.270 --> 02:27.500
I did.
And?

02:27.580 --> 02:28.569
There's a body.

02:28.640 --> 02:30.540
What? That can't be.

02:30.610 --> 02:32.009
I'm staring at it
right now.

02:32.080 --> 02:33.513
Put it on the jet.
Bring it here.

02:33.580 --> 02:34.717
I want confirmation.

02:34.780 --> 02:36.919
You want me to bring you
a decomposed body from Cuba?

02:36.990 --> 02:39.185
Yes. And hurry home, Dembe.

02:39.260 --> 02:42.184
Heddie's dying for a dance.
(CHUCKLES)

02:50.270 --> 02:51.692
(MRI MACHINE CLICKING)

02:51.770 --> 02:54.295
SAMAR: I went to the
neurologist for another MRI.

02:54.370 --> 02:57.908
The headaches,
the forgetfulness,
the confusion...

02:57.970 --> 03:02.578
It's all symptomatic
of something called
vascular dementia.

03:02.650 --> 03:06.575
Apparently I have been having
a series of mini-strokes.

03:06.650 --> 03:08.413
I don't feel them.
I don't know that
they're happening.

03:08.480 --> 03:11.881
But they are, and
each one causes damage.

03:13.660 --> 03:15.287
I'm glad you resigned.
That gives us the time

03:15.360 --> 03:16.884
to get you the treatment
that you need.

03:16.960 --> 03:18.257
It's not just work.

03:18.330 --> 03:20.753
It's family, too.
Aram, I can't have kids.

03:20.830 --> 03:22.718
Let's just stick to one major
life decision at a time.

03:22.800 --> 03:24.165
We have to talk
about this.

03:24.230 --> 03:26.937
And we will.
After you get better.

03:27.000 --> 03:30.106
**

03:30.170 --> 03:32.900
I'm up for anything
but false hope.

03:32.980 --> 03:34.675
No anger, no denial.

03:35.910 --> 03:38.549
No bargaining, no depression.
Can you do that for me?

03:41.520 --> 03:43.283
No.

03:43.350 --> 03:45.910
Okay, then please
promise me this.

03:45.990 --> 03:47.412
Don't tell anyone
about my condition.

03:47.490 --> 03:48.809
I don't want them to know.

03:49.590 --> 03:51.353
Of course.

03:51.430 --> 03:53.057
That I can do.

03:57.270 --> 03:59.431
REDDINGTON: Walt Whitman
lived in a boarding house

03:59.500 --> 04:01.991
at this address
during the Civil War.

04:02.070 --> 04:04.800
Did you know he was
an ardent prohibitionist?

04:04.870 --> 04:07.430
Imagine that,
a sober poet.

04:07.510 --> 04:09.102
(SLURPS) Mmm!

04:09.180 --> 04:11.842
Have I ever told you
about my mentor?

04:11.910 --> 04:15.539
You mean, somebody
actually taught you
how to drink this early?

04:15.620 --> 04:17.884
Is it early?
I thought it was late.

04:17.950 --> 04:19.315
Robert Vesco.

04:19.390 --> 04:21.813
Robert took me
under his wing.

04:21.890 --> 04:24.279
He taught me how
to be a fugitive.

04:24.360 --> 04:27.955
I trusted him with my life,
and my life's savings.

04:28.030 --> 04:31.022
Which he convinced me
to Invest

04:31.100 --> 04:34.695
in_a cattle ranch
In Paraguay.

04:34.770 --> 04:37.898
Or so I thought,
until I went down there

04:37.970 --> 04:39.631
_ and found out
It was a whorehouse

04:39.710 --> 04:41.405
just outside of Asuncion.

04:41.480 --> 04:43.402
He conned you.
Out of everything.

04:43.480 --> 04:46.347
I got my ﬁrst taste
for vengeance,

04:46.420 --> 04:48.718
which I was never
able to satisfy.

04:48.780 --> 04:49.883
Why not?

04:49.950 --> 04:52.453
Becaus_e Vesco
up and died on me.

04:53.460 --> 04:55.087
Robert Vesco
was a central player

04:55.160 --> 04:58.721
in American financial
and political scandals
in the 19705.

04:58.790 --> 05:01.588
In 1971, the SEC accused Vesco

05:01.660 --> 05:05.824
of looting $200 million out of
a mutual fund he controlled.

05:05.900 --> 05:09.336
And a year later,
Vesco made an illegal
campaign contribution

05:09.410 --> 05:11.002
to Richard Nixon,

05:11.070 --> 05:13.868
hoping that Nixon's
attorney general
would let him off the hook.

05:13.940 --> 05:16.101
And when he didn't,
Vesco fled the country,

05:16.180 --> 05:19.172
living the rest of his life in
glamorous exile in Costa Rica,

05:19.250 --> 05:21.070
Nicaragua, The Bahamas,
and Cuba,

05:21.150 --> 05:23.380
where he reportedly died
in 2007.

05:23.450 --> 05:25.543
Reportedly?
When Reddington
was in prison,

05:25.620 --> 05:27.053
he heard a rumor
that Vesco

05:27.120 --> 05:29.111
faked his death
to avoid capture.

05:29.190 --> 05:32.250
Does he have any proof?
He sent Dembe to Havana
to dig up his grave.

05:32.330 --> 05:33.558
He asked me
to have the ME.

05:33.630 --> 05:35.120
run the DNA on the remains
he unearthed.

05:35.200 --> 05:37.065
COOPER: There was a time
when the Bureau was actively

05:37.130 --> 05:38.927
hunting for Vesco,
but we're not anymore.

05:39.000 --> 05:40.297
If he did fake his death,

05:40.370 --> 05:42.702
I doubt it was
to avoid capture.
Reddington agrees.

05:42.770 --> 05:44.863
He thinks Vesco
found the De La Cruz,

05:44.940 --> 05:46.931
a Spanish Ship
filled with gold

05:47.010 --> 05:49.604
that sank off the coast
of Florida in the 17005.

05:49.680 --> 05:51.944
Vesco always told him that
if he found that treasure,

05:52.010 --> 05:53.546
that he would
disappear forever.

05:53.620 --> 05:55.440
Does Mr. Reddington
know him?
Know him?

05:55.520 --> 05:57.545
Vesco was Reddington's
mentor,

05:57.620 --> 05:59.815
until he swindled him
out of every penny he had

05:59.890 --> 06:02.154
and left him high and dry
in a whorehouse in Paraguay.

06:02.220 --> 06:04.324
I like this guy already.
COOPER: In the last 50 years,

06:04.390 --> 06:06.119
there have been two truly
mythic fugitives...

06:06.190 --> 06:07.896
Robert Vesco
and Raymond Reddington.

06:07.960 --> 06:10.463
If one can help us get
the other, I'm all for it.

06:10.530 --> 06:13.397
Ressler, Keen, find out
where the ME. is at
with the remains.

06:13.470 --> 06:16.564
Before you do that,
I want you to know
that I'm resigning.

06:16.640 --> 06:17.732
You're leaving?

06:17.810 --> 06:19.004
For what? The Mossad?

06:21.740 --> 06:22.900
COOPER:
Which reminds me...

06:22.980 --> 06:24.402
They've called to schedule
an exit interview.

06:25.510 --> 06:27.114
I know I speak for everyone
when I say

06:27.180 --> 06:29.614
we'll miss you
and we're happy for you.

06:29.690 --> 06:30.816
Thank you.

06:33.390 --> 06:36.848
Pop quiz... Guess who's
buried in Vesco's grave.

06:36.930 --> 06:38.921
So it's not Vesco?
No.

06:38.990 --> 06:40.651
His name was
Anderson Mount.

06:40.730 --> 06:43.119
Who's that?
Run-of—the-mill goon.

06:43.200 --> 06:44.690
His greatest hits.

06:44.770 --> 06:46.692
Did enough damage
to get into CODIS.

06:46.770 --> 06:48.988
And when we put
the DNA from the body

06:49.070 --> 06:50.662
into the system,
we got a match.

06:50.740 --> 06:52.298
RESSLER: Thanks, Doc.

06:52.370 --> 06:54.270
So, if Mount's
in Vesco's grave,

06:54.340 --> 06:56.035
maybe Vesco's
in Mount's life.

06:56.110 --> 06:59.341
It says in his file, Mount
was in Truro, Nova Scotia.

06:59.410 --> 07:00.513
If you want to
get off the grid,

07:00.580 --> 07:01.979
you can't get much
further than that.

07:02.050 --> 07:03.688
Looks like we're going
to Nova Scotia.

07:03.750 --> 07:06.787
In the middle of winter.
Come on.

07:06.860 --> 07:08.509
We're gonna need
warmer clothes.

07:13.730 --> 07:15.152
LEVI: Hello, Samar.

07:15.230 --> 07:17.118
Levi.
It's good to see you.

07:17.200 --> 07:19.168
I hear congratulations
are in order.

07:19.230 --> 07:21.630
Yeah. Can you believe it?
I'm engaged.

07:23.310 --> 07:25.164
Um, this is Dr. Sands.

07:25.240 --> 07:27.208
He will administer
the polygraph.

07:27.280 --> 07:28.907
Is this
really necessary?

07:28.980 --> 07:30.299
It's protocol.
You know that.

07:31.250 --> 07:33.070
Let me guess,
Tel Aviv regrets

07:33.150 --> 07:34.515
having loaned me out
to the FBI.

07:34.580 --> 07:36.480
They think my allegiances
have shifted.

07:36.550 --> 07:38.142
You have level-four
clearance.

07:38.220 --> 07:40.415
They want to make sure
I've kept what I know
from the Americans.

07:40.490 --> 07:44.028
Or Reddington. Hey.
I'm just the messenger.

07:44.090 --> 07:45.489
Yeah, and the message
I'm getting is that

07:45.560 --> 07:47.050
you think I have
something to hide.

07:50.930 --> 07:53.262
LIZ: So much _for
glamorous eXIle.

07:53.340 --> 07:54.739
I don't get it.
Why would Vesco

07:54.800 --> 07:58.361
fake his death so he could
live here of all places?

07:58.440 --> 08:00.499
I think we need to get
the local police involved.

08:00.580 --> 08:02.741
We talked about this.
Reddington said
a guy like Vesco

08:02.810 --> 08:05.404
would have every cop
in town on payroll.
We go to them,

08:05.480 --> 08:06.947
they tell Vesco,
and he slips away.

08:09.080 --> 08:12.243
**

08:12.320 --> 08:15.255
DR. SANDS: Have you
provided any classified
information to the FBI?

08:15.320 --> 08:18.027
SAMAR: No.
Were you loyal to
the state of Israel?

08:18.090 --> 08:19.955
Yes.
Have you broken any laws

08:20.030 --> 08:21.691
while working with
Raymond Reddington?

08:21.760 --> 08:24.092
Yes.
Have you withheld
any information

08:24.170 --> 08:27.435
from your Mossad handlers?
Yes.

08:27.500 --> 08:30.731
Information about
your reSIgnatIon?
Yes.

08:30.810 --> 08:33.574
Have you Shared it
with the FBI?
0.

08:33.640 --> 08:36.370
Is this personal
information?
Yes.

08:36.440 --> 08:38.271
Do you have any
serious medical issues?

08:40.050 --> 08:41.142
Yes.

08:42.820 --> 08:43.809
What is it?

08:46.190 --> 08:47.487
I'm pregnant.

08:49.360 --> 08:52.158
Vesco, or whatever
he's calling himself,

08:52.230 --> 08:54.755
he would have the resources
to go anywhere he wanted to,

08:54.830 --> 08:56.593
create any life.
(KE'I'I'LE WHISTLING)

08:56.670 --> 08:58.558
Whatever brought him here,
it's personal.

08:58.630 --> 09:02.168
RESSLER: Well, you can ask him
all the questions you want
once we find him.

09:02.240 --> 09:03.639
First, we got to
clear those kids.

09:03.710 --> 09:05.769
Something about this guy,
what Reddington told us,

09:05.840 --> 09:07.205
it doesn't add up.

09:07.280 --> 09:10.101
(KE'ITLE WHISTLING)

09:10.180 --> 09:12.398
(WHISTLING STOPS)

09:13.680 --> 09:15.216
(KE'ITLE CLA'I'I'ERS)

09:18.750 --> 09:20.980
(CELL PHONE RINGING)

09:21.060 --> 09:23.324
**

09:24.760 --> 09:26.899
(RINGING CONTINUES)

09:34.740 --> 09:37.004
Yeah.
MAN: One unmarked outside.

09:37.070 --> 09:39.129
Two agents just entered
your building.

09:39.210 --> 09:40.802
Exit down the alley
to the east.

09:40.880 --> 09:42.177
Will advise.

09:43.510 --> 09:45.444
**

09:53.360 --> 09:55.681
(CAT MEOWS)

10:01.960 --> 10:04.520
He's on the move!
Alley to the east! On foot!

10:07.470 --> 10:09.097
MAN: Exit the alley
and turn right.

10:15.380 --> 10:16.404
Street's clear.

10:17.750 --> 10:18.978
Keen, tell me
you got something.

10:19.050 --> 10:20.847
Head south
towards the shoreline.

10:20.920 --> 10:22.569
Crossing Acadia Street!
Headed east!

10:22.650 --> 10:23.912
Blue denim. Tan sweater.

10:26.250 --> 10:27.478
Stop!

10:27.560 --> 10:29.050
MAN: Get in.

10:32.930 --> 10:35.228
Robert.
(PANTING)

10:35.300 --> 10:38.519
Stop!
(TIRES SCREECH)

10:38.600 --> 10:39.931
LIZ: (SCOFFS) Reddington.

10:43.010 --> 10:47.003
Like I said,
whatever brought him here,
it's personal.

10:49.310 --> 10:52.074
REDDINGTON: You look
awfully good
for a dead man.

10:52.150 --> 10:53.674
Where the hell's
my money?

10:55.280 --> 10:57.180
**

10:57.250 --> 10:59.343
Are you still upset
about Asuncion?

10:59.920 --> 11:01.911
I trusted you.

11:01.990 --> 11:03.628
You were my mentor.

11:03.690 --> 11:07.251
And I was mentoring you in
survival, in being selfish.

11:07.330 --> 11:08.695
And looking out
for yourself.

11:08.760 --> 11:11.194
Robert. My money.

11:11.270 --> 11:13.465
You think I'd be living
in Nova Scotia if I had it?

11:13.540 --> 11:14.962
I know why
you're living there.

11:15.040 --> 11:17.531
You found the De La Cruz.

11:17.610 --> 11:19.339
The treasure.
Where is it?

11:21.180 --> 11:24.638
If it's real, I believe
I know where it is.

11:25.880 --> 11:27.438
I never went after it.

11:27.520 --> 11:30.284
Oh, I wanted to,
but enemies were circling.

11:30.350 --> 11:31.647
I had to flee.

11:33.390 --> 11:36.314
So I staged my own death
and I fled the country.

11:38.530 --> 11:40.418
And by the time
the dust had settled,

11:40.500 --> 11:44.129
I... I realized
that I had changed.

11:44.200 --> 11:46.088
"Changed."
I'd lost the itch.

11:46.170 --> 11:47.239
I walked away.

11:47.300 --> 11:49.734
Being forced to lie low
and live the simple life

11:49.810 --> 11:51.732
was the best thing that
could've happened to me.

11:51.810 --> 11:55.132
I-It forced me to turn
the world off
and to tune into myself.

11:55.210 --> 11:57.576
Oh, my God.
I have my cat.

11:57.650 --> 11:59.572
I have plenty of
glorious books.

11:59.650 --> 12:02.915
Robert, you conned me once.
I won't be conned again.

12:02.990 --> 12:05.515
Untether yourself from
social expectations

12:05.590 --> 12:09.151
and this destructive life of
crime and... And look inward.

12:09.220 --> 12:12.257
I'm happy to.
Right after I get the gold.

12:14.400 --> 12:16.527
You can have it, Ray,
but... (SIGHS)

12:16.600 --> 12:18.158
It won't give you
inner peace.

12:18.230 --> 12:20.790
I already have
inner peace.

12:20.870 --> 12:22.690
What I could use
IS a new yacht.

12:22.770 --> 12:24.931
The last one was seized
In Mallorca.

12:25.010 --> 12:28.173
All right, I believe
the gold is buried

12:28.240 --> 12:32.142
under the Old French
Opera House
in New Orleans.

12:32.210 --> 12:33.643
I can prove it to you,

12:33.720 --> 12:35.813
but we'll have to
reroute the jet.

12:35.880 --> 12:37.984
To where?
Washington.

12:38.050 --> 12:43.226
There isn't a treasure map,
_ but there is a clue trail
In the LIbrary of Congress.

12:43.290 --> 12:45.155
Robert, if you're lying,

12:45.230 --> 12:48.791
I will shatter your serenity
by burning your home,

12:48.860 --> 12:52.023
drowning your cat,
and cutting off your big toes.

12:52.100 --> 12:54.239
You wouldn't dare
drown my cat.

12:54.300 --> 12:55.892
(CHUCKLES) Maybe not.

12:55.970 --> 12:58.200
But I will take the toes.

13:03.780 --> 13:04.872
(KNOCK ON DOOR)
ARAM: How'd it go?

13:04.950 --> 13:06.542
They sent Levi.

13:06.610 --> 13:08.419
A friendly face
to put me at ease

13:08.480 --> 13:09.913
while they administered
a polygraph.

13:09.990 --> 13:12.015
They gave you
a polygraph? Why?

13:12.090 --> 13:14.251
To make I wasn't leaving
because I'd been turned.

13:14.320 --> 13:16.083
That's ridiculous.
And insulting.

13:16.160 --> 13:18.253
Listen, Aram, I meant
what I said earlier

13:18.330 --> 13:19.854
about having children.
