What took you so long?

27:25.170 --> 27:26.899
This big guy
won't let me past!

27:26.970 --> 27:28.835
He says he has a delivery.
I've got it all.

27:28.910 --> 27:31.071
Everything from wet wipes
to adult diapers.

27:31.150 --> 27:33.710
I got your Maalox,
your Mylanta,
your Kaopectate.

27:33.780 --> 27:34.917
II got a vaporizer...

27:34.980 --> 27:36.447
Those things don't even
all do the same thing!

27:36.520 --> 27:39.739
What's going on?
All I know is I got
a call 45 minutes ago

27:39.820 --> 27:41.708
saying Count
someone-or-another
had the runs.

27:41.790 --> 27:43.052
It's for Count Almaviva.

27:43.120 --> 27:44.724
Rolando, he's come down
with the flu.

27:44.790 --> 27:47.258
What did he eat?
Maybe he got a bad oyster.

27:47.330 --> 27:49.890
(GROANS) I had a nasty
Blue Point once.

27:49.960 --> 27:51.461
Ohh, turned me
inside out.

27:51.530 --> 27:53.122
I was playing tango
with the toilet

27:53.200 --> 27:54.462
for the better part
of a day.

27:54.540 --> 27:56.929
(VOCALIZING)
* One, two, three
One, two, three *

27:57.000 --> 27:58.865
Fascinating as this is,
we need to get you
to the Count now.

27:58.940 --> 28:00.168
He's on in 10.

28:02.140 --> 28:04.540
(VOCALIZING)

28:12.220 --> 28:13.642
(WHIRRING)

28:16.990 --> 28:18.321
(CLA'I'I'ERING)

28:18.390 --> 28:19.721
* Tutti mi vogliono

28:19.790 --> 28:21.155
* Donne, ragazzi

28:21.230 --> 28:22.891
* Vecchi, fanciulle

28:22.960 --> 28:24.268
* Qua la parrucca

28:24.330 --> 28:25.797
* Presto la barba

28:25.870 --> 28:27.292
* Qua la sanguigna

28:27.370 --> 28:28.496
Cue Vontae and Dembe!

28:28.570 --> 28:29.764
Step-ball-change,

28:29.840 --> 28:32.138
step-ball-change,
step-ball-change.

28:32.210 --> 28:34.974
**

28:35.040 --> 28:37.770
* Figaro *

28:37.850 --> 28:39.147
Ruddiger,
what the hell's going on?

28:39.210 --> 28:40.973
(VOICE BREAKING)
The voice.

28:41.050 --> 28:43.610
The heartbreak and sorrow!

28:43.680 --> 28:46.012
Ah.
It's a comedy!

28:46.090 --> 28:48.251
No, my sorrow!

28:48.320 --> 28:52.427
When I was a boy,
all my friends wanted
to be football players

28:52.490 --> 28:55.596
and racecar drivers,
and I dreamed to be a tenor!

28:55.660 --> 28:57.628
Oh, dear God.
This is bad, Ray.

28:57.700 --> 28:59.964
I'm sorry, Raymond.
I lost my place!

29:00.030 --> 29:01.497
The music,
it took me back!

29:01.570 --> 29:04.505
We're on a clock!
We're timed to the music.

29:04.570 --> 29:07.107
If the detonation
doesn't go off exactly
with the applause,

29:07.170 --> 29:08.205
everyone will hear it!

29:08.280 --> 29:10.032
I'm so sorry!
Okay, that's it.

29:10.110 --> 29:11.873
Set the charges.
Robert, give us a hand.

29:11.950 --> 29:14.009
Ray, we don't have time
to set all the charges.

29:14.080 --> 29:16.469
He's nearing the end
of the aria now.
(RUDDIGER SOBS)

29:16.550 --> 29:20.884
(VOCALIZING)

29:20.960 --> 29:24.282
Glen!
We have a situation.

29:24.360 --> 29:26.783
(SIGHS) What situation?
(APPLAUSE)

29:26.860 --> 29:28.725
REDDINGTON: We're behind,
and if we blow
the charges late,

29:28.800 --> 29:30.199
we're gonna have
the police here in seconds.

29:30.260 --> 29:32.694
We need a distraction.
Something loud. Really loud!

29:32.770 --> 29:35.136
What the hell do you
want me to do?
I don't know, Glen!

29:35.200 --> 29:37.293
That's why you're here!
You wanted a second chance!

29:37.370 --> 29:40.464
This is it! Figure it out!
Think fast! Make some noise!

29:40.540 --> 29:42.974
(BOTH SINGING IN ITALIAN)

29:43.040 --> 29:45.372
**

29:46.580 --> 29:50.641
It's time to make your...
Broadway debut.

29:51.120 --> 29:52.417
(BEEP)

29:59.290 --> 30:02.350
Fire! Fire!

30:02.430 --> 30:04.398
(AUDIENCE MURMURING)
Everybody out!

30:04.470 --> 30:07.189
There's a grease fire
in the kitchen! It ain't good!

30:07.270 --> 30:09.067
(AUDIENCE SHOUTING)

30:09.140 --> 30:11.165
(ALARM RINGING)

30:11.240 --> 30:14.175
**

30:14.240 --> 30:15.673
(BEEP)

30:15.740 --> 30:20.609
Run for your lives!
Run for your lives!

30:20.680 --> 30:21.908
Blow it. Now!

30:21.980 --> 30:24.312
(BEEP, EXPLOSION)

30:41.270 --> 30:43.465
Oh, my God.

30:43.540 --> 30:45.007
The De La Cruz.

30:45.610 --> 30:47.259
It is real.

30:49.380 --> 30:51.940
(CHUCKLES) Now, there's
the twinkle in your eye

30:52.010 --> 30:53.705
I've been looking for.

30:53.780 --> 30:55.839
(LAUGHS)

31:02.690 --> 31:04.749
Sir, what on Earth would make
you shout "fire" in the middle

31:04.830 --> 31:07.924
of a crowded theater when
in fact there was no fire?

31:08.000 --> 31:10.798
Ithought
I smelled smoke.

31:10.860 --> 31:13.090
All I was trying to do
was save lives!

31:13.170 --> 31:14.933
RESSLER: I'm telling you,
Keen, he double-crossed us.

31:15.000 --> 31:17.230
We're not getting Vesco
or the money.

31:17.300 --> 31:19.109
He gave me his word.
I believe him.

31:19.170 --> 31:21.274
Is that it?
Last one. Time to roll.

31:21.340 --> 31:22.602
RESSLER: Look, I'll talk
to the local PD.

31:22.680 --> 31:24.944
See what they have to say.
I'll talk to fire.

31:25.010 --> 31:26.807
**

31:26.880 --> 31:29.747
Mr. Carter.
FIREMAN: You know this guy?

31:29.820 --> 31:32.118
Elizabeth Keen, FBI.
Can I talk to him
for a minute?

31:32.190 --> 31:33.487
(RADIO CHATTER)

31:34.560 --> 31:36.755
Hey! What are the odds
of seeing you here?

31:36.820 --> 31:39.152
You an opera fan?
Drop the act. Where is he?

31:39.230 --> 31:40.925
Don't know what
you're talking about.

31:41.000 --> 31:43.321
Reddington. He was here.
How long ago?

31:43.400 --> 31:44.492
Don't lie to me.

31:45.730 --> 31:47.561
You just missed him.

31:52.910 --> 31:54.832
(CELL PHONE RINGING)

31:56.680 --> 31:57.829
Elizabeth.

31:57.910 --> 32:00.504
This isn't a good time.
I'm at the opera house.

32:00.580 --> 32:01.717
Did you enjoy the show?

32:01.780 --> 32:03.577
You got your treasure.
Now I want Vesco.

32:07.420 --> 32:09.854
We'll be at Lulu's enjoying
their key lime pie.

32:09.920 --> 32:11.251
I'll get your Slice to go.

32:13.030 --> 32:14.258
(CELL PHONE BEEPS)
(SIGHS)

32:15.100 --> 32:16.397
Sex and treasure.

32:17.760 --> 32:20.194
People will betray
for both.

32:20.270 --> 32:24.058
Like you're betraying me now
that I've gotten you the gold.

32:24.140 --> 32:25.835
You can turn me in
at Lulu's,

32:25.910 --> 32:28.174
and your revenge
will be complete.

32:31.650 --> 32:33.379
More, I understand.

32:34.620 --> 32:38.317
You were my protege, Ray.
I loved you.

32:39.620 --> 32:42.418
But I took you for
everything you were worth,

32:42.490 --> 32:45.186
and I left you in
an Asuncion whorehouse,

32:45.260 --> 32:47.854
and I never gave it
a second thought.

32:47.930 --> 32:49.352
And now?

32:49.430 --> 32:51.068
Now I'm free.

32:51.130 --> 32:53.462
**

32:56.500 --> 32:59.663
I have no intention of
turnIng you In, Robert.

32:59.740 --> 33:01.571
And we're certainly
not going to Lulu's.

33:01.640 --> 33:03.198
Place is bursting
with tourists,

33:03.280 --> 33:04.702
and their pies
are terrible.

33:04.780 --> 33:06.577
We're gonna go find
ourselves a nice,

33:06.650 --> 33:07.901
quiet cup of coffee
somewhere.

33:11.350 --> 33:15.514
Is it true that you introduced
Nixon's brother to Castro

33:15.590 --> 33:17.353
and then
swindled them both

33:17.420 --> 33:20.025
into investing in
a bogus drug trial?

33:20.090 --> 33:22.627
And got tossed in a Cuban jail
for my troubles.

33:22.700 --> 33:25.225
(LAUGHS)
Nixon and Castro!

33:25.300 --> 33:28.394
My God!
It boggles the mind.

33:28.470 --> 33:30.392
Truck'S in the warehouse.

33:30.470 --> 33:32.438
Locked tighter than
a clam at high tide.

33:32.510 --> 33:33.738
Where are the others?
(KEYS CLA'I'I'ER)

33:33.810 --> 33:35.402
Killin' bourbon
on Bourbon Street.

33:35.480 --> 33:38.449
Why don't you join them?
(LAUGHS) Hoo!

33:38.510 --> 33:44.119
Well, boys, I am off
for a night of debauchery
in the Big Easy.

33:44.190 --> 33:46.249
Like Blanche DuBois,

33:46.320 --> 33:49.653
I depend on the kindness
of strangers.

33:49.720 --> 33:51.221
Cheerio!

33:51.290 --> 33:52.621
(REDDINGTON CHUCKLES)

33:54.500 --> 33:57.594
Well, I feel like
a walk by the river.

33:57.660 --> 33:59.423
That's a great idea.

33:59.500 --> 34:01.889
Oh, I'm afraid I wouldn't
be very good company.

34:02.640 --> 34:05.404
I'm old. I'm tired.

34:05.470 --> 34:07.131
And I'm at peace.

34:08.080 --> 34:09.433
The airport, then.

34:09.510 --> 34:11.148
Tomorrow at 10:00.

34:11.210 --> 34:12.905
I'll drop you
wherever you want.

34:14.080 --> 34:18.449
I was filled with vengeance
for so long,

34:18.520 --> 34:22.411
I never saw the gift
you gave me in Asuncion.

34:23.720 --> 34:27.349
I never trusted anyone
easily after that.

34:27.430 --> 34:28.920
That's why
I'm still alive.

34:30.060 --> 34:31.698
I'm in your debt,
my friend.

34:32.930 --> 34:34.238
Ohh.

34:37.170 --> 34:38.660
Believe me, Ray.

34:39.770 --> 34:41.829
You've more than repaid
your debt.

34:41.910 --> 34:44.242
**

34:51.950 --> 34:53.281
(CELL PHONE SPEED-DIALS)

34:54.050 --> 34:55.278
Change of plans.

34:57.060 --> 34:59.085
I just got off
the phone with Levi.

34:59.160 --> 35:01.526
I have been honorably
discharged.

35:01.600 --> 35:03.522
I'm, uh, not surprised.
I am.

35:03.600 --> 35:05.329
During the polygraph test
when he asked me

35:05.400 --> 35:07.061
why I was leaving,
I said it was personal.

35:07.130 --> 35:09.189
I didn't want him to know
the truth, so I lied.

35:09.270 --> 35:11.602
Well, whatever you told him,
it's over.

35:11.670 --> 35:13.900
So now we can talk.

35:15.580 --> 35:16.808
About you being pregnant.

35:20.980 --> 35:23.574
Aram...
That's what you've been
trying to tell me, isn't it?

35:23.650 --> 35:24.742
(CLA'I'I'ERING)

35:24.820 --> 35:26.048
(RATI'LING)

35:26.120 --> 35:29.157
So, my parents
made this for me

35:29.220 --> 35:32.428
thirty years ago for the day
I became a dad.

35:32.490 --> 35:35.994
Uh, all I, uh, remember
are the fruit-flies

35:36.060 --> 35:38.665
and the, uh, cheesecloth.
(LAUGHS)

35:38.730 --> 35:41.858
And the fancy crystal that
my mom insists on using

35:41.940 --> 35:44.033
nine months from now
when we pop the cork

35:44.100 --> 35:47.866
_to celebrate
unImagInable love.

35:49.380 --> 35:51.507
**

35:54.680 --> 35:56.841
I'm not pregnant, Aram.

35:56.920 --> 35:59.445
That was the lie
that I told Levi

35:59.520 --> 36:01.010
to cover the truth
about my health.

36:04.090 --> 36:05.626
You're not...

36:11.530 --> 36:14.567
The truth is that I've never
wanted children.

36:14.640 --> 36:16.631
I used to be self-conscious
about that, about the fact

36:16.700 --> 36:20.966
that I didn't have any
kind of maternal instinct.

36:21.040 --> 36:23.975
But I made my peace with it
a long time ago.

36:25.510 --> 36:27.808
And then I met you.

36:27.880 --> 36:29.347
And you changed everything.

36:30.850 --> 36:35.082
And now there's nothing
I would like more
than to be pregnant.

36:35.160 --> 36:37.958
Nothing either of us
would like more.

36:40.790 --> 36:42.348
But it can't happen.

36:44.130 --> 36:46.394
I can't raise a child.

36:47.700 --> 36:48.792
Even

36:52.710 --> 36:53.802
Okay.

36:54.640 --> 36:56.403
Okay?

36:56.480 --> 36:58.846
If you don't think
we should have kids,
then we shouldn't have them.

36:58.910 --> 37:01.003
You say that now, Aram,
but in a year or five years...

37:01.080 --> 37:02.672
I'll be saying
the same thing.
No.

37:05.090 --> 37:06.978
Someday you will
have regrets,

37:07.050 --> 37:08.711
and I don't want to
be the reason why.

37:12.090 --> 37:16.390
Aram, that's why
I've been wanting to talk.

37:27.210 --> 37:28.734
I think you deserve more.

37:41.050 --> 37:42.358
That's quite
the little stunt you pulled.

37:42.420 --> 37:43.819
REDDINGTON:
It was, wasn't it?

37:43.890 --> 37:46.552
I was quite pleased with
how it all came together.

37:46.630 --> 37:47.654
LIZ: Where's Vesco?

37:47.730 --> 37:49.527
He inside?
No, he's not.

37:49.600 --> 37:52.068
The treasure is.
You let him go.

37:52.130 --> 37:53.666
Turns out, he's reformed.

37:53.730 --> 37:56.290
(LAUGHS)
A reformed fugitive.

37:56.370 --> 37:58.463
Sworn off greed
and avarice.

37:58.540 --> 38:00.303
LIZ: So you commuted
his sentence

38:00.370 --> 38:01.837
like the President
commuted yours?

38:01.910 --> 38:04.845
Yes, and in honor
of his ascetic existence,

38:04.910 --> 38:08.471
I've decided to hand over
$100-something million

38:08.550 --> 38:11.747
worth of
18th-century gold.

38:11.820 --> 38:13.310
You're just gonna
give it to us?

38:13.390 --> 38:15.756
Every last doubloon.
It's inside.

38:20.230 --> 38:21.219
Or it isn't.

38:25.270 --> 38:26.965
(LAUGHS)

38:29.070 --> 38:30.992
I'm in your debt,
my friend.

38:31.070 --> 38:34.904
VESCO: Ohh.
Believe me, Ray.

38:37.410 --> 38:39.139
You've more than repaid
your debt.

38:42.350 --> 38:45.114
LIZ: (LAUGHS)
He's reformed, is he?

38:45.190 --> 38:47.283
"Given up greed
and avarice"?

38:47.950 --> 38:49.713
**

38:49.790 --> 38:51.451
Do you have a phone?
(LAUGHS)

38:51.530 --> 38:54.749
(LAUGHING) I'm sure
he'll be a real ascetic
with your $100 million.

38:56.300 --> 38:58.393
Come on.
Take my picture.

38:58.470 --> 39:00.722
It's not often
I get egg on my face.

39:00.800 --> 39:03.462
But to be egged
by the same person twice?

39:03.540 --> 39:05.462
That needs memorializing.

39:05.540 --> 39:06.700
RESSLER:
You think this is funny?

39:06.770 --> 39:09.102
This was a complete
waste of time.

39:09.180 --> 39:10.704
Waste of time?

39:10.780 --> 39:13.044
We've been
decrypting legends.

39:13.110 --> 39:14.646
Chasing pirates.

39:14.720 --> 39:16.870
Hunting hidden treasure.

39:16.950 --> 39:18.986
And come up empty.
We lost Vesco.

39:19.050 --> 39:21.655
How can you lose
something you never had?

39:21.720 --> 39:24.280
I gave you a Blacklister
you thought was dead.

39:24.360 --> 39:27.659
Now that you know he's alive,
you can hunt him down.

39:27.730 --> 39:30.255
Plus, you witnessed
my humiliation.

39:30.330 --> 39:32.389
I think that would salve
any wound.

39:32.470 --> 39:33.994
It doesn't.
But it's a start.

39:35.000 --> 39:36.467
Get in here, Dembe.

39:36.540 --> 39:38.405
I see a little yolk
on your cheek.

39:39.740 --> 39:40.832
(SIGHS)

39:41.710 --> 39:43.337
Smile, suckers.

39:45.750 --> 39:47.001
(CAMERA SHUTTER CLICKS)

39:47.080 --> 39:48.911
(LIZ LAUGHING)

39:48.980 --> 39:50.743
(LAUGHING)

39:54.350 --> 39:56.181
(LAUGHING)

40:00.230 --> 40:02.357
(FOOTSTEPS APPROACH)

40:15.240 --> 40:18.004
You're wrong about me.
How did you find me?

40:18.080 --> 40:20.503
When you said there's
nothing I want more
than to have a child.

40:21.280 --> 40:22.542
I mean, that is...

40:22.620 --> 40:27.614
That is what I thought,
what I had always imagined.

40:30.590 --> 40:31.727
Until I met you.

40:33.890 --> 40:37.223
And then you changed
everything.

40:39.230 --> 40:40.527
What we have...

40:41.300 --> 40:42.597
This is our story,

40:44.540 --> 40:48.408
and if our story doesn't
involve having kids,

40:48.480 --> 40:51.176
well, that's okay.

40:51.240 --> 40:53.970
* Tell_ me there's
nothIng to fear

40:54.050 --> 40:57.019
I don't need
to wait nine months

40:57.080 --> 41:01.414
_to celebrate
unImagInable love.

41:01.490 --> 41:06.120
And I certainly don't need
fancy crystal.

41:09.230 --> 41:11.528
Aram.
We are never
breaking up. Okay?

41:11.600 --> 41:13.898
Like, ever.

41:13.970 --> 41:16.234
And I don't_ want
any denIal,

41:16.300 --> 41:19.428
anger, bargaining,
or depression.

41:21.110 --> 41:22.338
Only acceptance.

41:24.980 --> 41:26.277
Can you do that for me?

41:27.780 --> 41:29.008
No.

41:32.150 --> 41:33.185
Okay.

41:36.120 --> 41:37.519
Promise me this...

41:38.860 --> 41:41.522
That you will do everything
humanly possible

41:41.600 --> 41:44.091
to try and get better.

41:45.170 --> 41:47.195
**

41:47.270 --> 41:48.419
I promise.

41:48.500 --> 41:50.730
* I'll tell you what
you want to hear

41:50.800 --> 41:54.236
* I'm not gonna go nowhere

41:54.310 --> 41:57.029
* I'm not gonna
break your plans

41:57.110 --> 41:58.407
ARAM: It's gonna be okay.

41:58.480 --> 42:00.641
* I could never disappear

42:00.710 --> 42:02.018
Tell me that again.

42:04.480 --> 42:06.311
Everything's gonna be okay.

42:07.220 --> 42:10.485
**

42:22.900 --> 42:24.959
**
